reviewText: Course content is restricted and does not truly include a certification without a paid upgrade. This is advertised as a free course...

While the content is okay, it only scratches the surface of almost all topics that are discussed. Need a bit more depth. The peer reviews is dreadful: there are not enough fellow students to review work on time so I had to reset my deadlines four times. Money in your bank, Coursera! A month later I still have not been able to pass the last two assignments because no one will review my work, so I can't finish the course.
The instructional style and content fell flat compared to the first session in this certificate (Culture Driven teams). The peer-reviewed assignments were a waste of time.

The content of the course is interesting and the videos are easy to follow. Every week ends with a quiz, an assignment that needs to be completed and you're also required to review your peers in the class. The problem is that usually, you end up doing the quiz and the assignment in one day, and then you're forced to wait days/weeks until someone else submits an assignment you can review. So even though you're basically finished with 95% of the course you're stuck waiting and not knowing when you'll be able to finish. In theory, I suppose you could wait months if nobody else takes the course.

The assigned readings in this course were limited to short online articles, mostly by the course instructors, that re-stated, but did not really expand on the course material. There is a lot of material available on emotional intelligence and mindfulness that could better enrich the lecture material and improve the course.
Some excellent insights, albeit a bit too superficial in my view. Would have loved to see some concepts explored more in depth

I am an IT Director at a small Architecture/Engineering firm and keeping an IT team engaged and innovative can be very challenging in this environment.  The steps you outlined have been very helpful, both from a personal emotional intelligence perspective as well as a team management perspective.  I plan to implement improved strategies and checklists specifically based on this training.  Professors Legatt and Newberry have a clear understanding of the topic, and the ability to convey the message in a clear and concise manner.  Thank you.

This is my first on-line course on soft skill.  It was a great experience going through it with commitment to complete the course.  The given assignments and peers' review made you think through what you have learnt from the modules.  My key take away is the charting system (RACI matrix) which help ensure that all aspects of a plan  are identified, managed and completed efficiently and effectively in Team Building; & the key lessons from IDEO's that drive performance:  ask the right questions, prototype your ideas, collect feedback, and learn from failure.
